        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Juni 13, 1852</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Mr I. Leeser</addressee>!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p>As I purpose to visit <placeName>Europa</placeName> in a few Weeks<lb/> I was
                    <sic>atvised</sic> by mine Relations here, to<lb/> fetch my marriage
                    <sic>certificat</sic>, signed by the<lb/> proper <sic>authoratys</sic>, along
                with me, supposing<lb/> all the time, that I got the same in my possession,<lb/> I
                found by searching all my papers, that I been<lb/> sadly mistaken, and I
                    <sic>distinktly</sic>
                <sic>remembre</sic> now,<lb/> that the same is in the Hands, of my Brother<lb/>
                <persName>Jacob Dessan</persName> in <placeName><sic>Calafornia</sic></placeName>,
                You therefore<lb/> see the <sic>Neccesity</sic> of my applying to you,<lb/> for a
                    <sic>doublicate</sic> certificate, for <sic>wich</sic> you<lb/> will
                    <sic>extreemly</sic> oblige me, <sic>anny</sic> possible<lb/> expense this may
                    <sic>occure</sic>, <sic>pleas</sic>
                <sic>Sine</sic> and state<lb/> it to me, as I of course shall <add>?</add><lb/> the
                same, with the greatest thanks and pleasure.<lb/> I suppose if the same is written
                in German, it would<lb/> best <sic>answere</sic> the purpose; hoping that you<lb/>
                enjoy good health and prosperity, and also that<lb/> you will be not annoyed, at my
                taxing your kindness,</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">I remain Sire,</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Your's <persName role="author">Isaak Ederheimer</persName></p>
            <p>my <sic>direktion</sic>.</p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Nro 22. Oliver St.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
